# Playwright Configuration Reference

## playwright.config.ts

```typescript
testDir: "./tests"
fullyParallel: true
forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI
retries: ENV.RETRIES                    // 2 in CI, 1 local
workers: ENV.WORKERS                    // Default 1

browser: "chromium" (channel: "msedge") // Always Edge
baseURL: ENV.BASE_URL
storageState: ENV.STORAGE_STATE_PATH    // .auth/storage-state.json

trace: "retain-on-failure"
screenshot: "only-on-failure"
video: "retain-on-failure"
actionTimeout: 20000
navigationTimeout: 45000

globalSetup: "./src/config/global-setup.ts"
timeout: ENV.TIMEOUT                    // From .env (typically 60000)
expect.timeout: 15000
outputDir: "test-results"
```

## Reporters

| Reporter | Config | CI Only? |
|---|---|---|
| HTML | `open: "never"`, `outputFolder: "playwright-report"` | No |
| List | `printSteps: true` | No |
| Custom Dashboard | `./src/reporters/custom-dashboard.reporter.ts` | No |
| JUnit XML | `outputFile: "test-results/junit-results.xml"` | Yes |

## globalSetup Flow

1. Check if credentials exist → skip if not
2. If `NUKE_PROFILE=true` → delete `.auth/` and `.edge-profile/`
3. Check `.auth/storage-state.json` age → skip if < 1 hour
4. Verify `.edge-profile/Default/Preferences` exists → error with instructions if not
5. Launch persistent Edge context → headless
6. Check if already logged in (URL doesn't contain `/login`)
7. If not → perform MSAL + TOTP login
8. Save storageState → close context

## Timeout Hierarchy

```
Global test timeout:  ENV.TIMEOUT (60000ms default)
Navigation timeout:   45000ms
Action timeout:       20000ms
Expect timeout:       15000ms
```

## Project Structure

Single project named `e2e-tests` matching all `*.spec.ts` files.

No separate "setup" project – globalSetup handles auth. The `auth.setup.ts` file in fixtures is available as an alternative but currently unused in the config.
